scientific inquirers place the origin of Kabbala in the twelfth century,
though mysticism akin to it appears as early as Bible times. On the
great influence of the Kabbala in Middle Ages cf. Stöckl, *Gesch. d.
Philos. im Mittelalter*. Bnd. ii. On the Talmud at the time of writing
three monographs are about to appear--Prof. Strack separately; Dr.
Ginsburg in Smith-Wace, *Dict. of* 

